title: Several people killed in Hamburg shooting
description: Several people have been killed in a shooting in the northern German city of Hamburg.

title: Three wounded in Tel Aviv after gunman opened fire in suspected terror attack
description: Three people have been wounded after a Palestinian gunman opened fire on a crowded street in Tel Aviv before being shot and killed, Israeli officials said.

title: First map of insect brain signals 'big step forward' in understanding thoughts
description: A map of the 3,016 neurons that make up a baby fruit fly's brain is the first of its kind, according to a new study.

title: 'I want Putin to die', says shaken grandmother after missile hit apartment block car park
description: I met Larysa standing on broken glass outside her Kyiv apartment block trying to convince two council workmen to come up to her flat and mend her shattered windows.

title: Nigerian politician's alleged organ harvesting plot was to avoid risk to relatives, trial told
description: A senior Nigerian politician tried to bring a street trader to the UK to harvest his kidney because it was "far better to buy one" than find a family member to donate the organ, a court has heard.

title: 'The sky is the limit': Discovery could see devices literally create energy from thin air
description: Devices that literally create energy from thin air could be made real thanks to a newly-discovered enzyme that transforms hydrogen into an electrical current, scientists have said.

title: Ex-US Marine in tears as he describes 'catastrophe' of US withdrawal from Afghanistan
description: Active service members and veterans have described in harrowing detail the carnage and death they witnessed during the chaotic US withdrawal from Afghanistan.

title: Three arrested after spate of 'sushi terrorism' in Japan
description: Three people have been arrested following a spate of "sushi terrorism" videos posted online in Japan.

title: Constipation, bloating, and diarrhoea among long COVID symptoms
description: Catching COVID-19 can cause long-term gastrointestinal problems such as constipation and diarrhoea, a study has found.

title: China hits out at Dutch plan to limit export of semiconductor tech
description: China has criticised a Dutch plan to restrict the export of semiconductor equipment - a vital part of the high-tech supply chain.

title: Ibiza dengue fever outbreak prompts summer warning from health officials
description: People planning to travel to Ibiza over the summer are being warned of an increased risk of dengue fever after an outbreak on the Spanish island.

title: Georgia drops controversial 'foreign agent' bill after two days of violent protests
description: Georgia's ruling party said it will drop a controversial bill on "foreign agents" after two days of violent protests.

title: Fiddler on the Roof actor Chaim Topol dies aged 87
description: Fiddler on the Roof actor Chaim Topol has died at the age of 87.

title: Five killed in Russian airstrikes across Ukraine
description: Russia has launched a massive missile attack across Ukraine - striking targets in the capital Kyiv, the second biggest city of Kharkiv and the Black Sea port of Odesa - with at least five people killed.
